            "body": "> You didn't set the mapping in Normal mode.\n\nas suggested I missed `'i'` in setting the keymap:\n\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set({'n', 'i', 'x', 's'}, '<F5>',\n  function()\n    print(vim.fn.mode(1))\n  end)\n```\n\nWith this last setting I get:\n\n     1. v<F5> → 'v'\n     2. i<C-o>v<F5> → 'v'\n     3. v<C-g><F5> → 's'\n     4. i<C-o>v<C-g><F5> → 's'\n    (5. i<C-o><F5> → 'niI')\n\nBut, I would need to check if we are in a pure Visual mode or in a *insert-visual mode* (case 1 vs 2) or the same for Select (case 3 vs 4). I don't know if it could be possible...or maybe an autocommand is needed for tracking mode changes.",
